    "descriptionModule": {
      "briefSummary": "This is a research study of a new experimental drug called darusentan. Darusentan is not currently approved by the United States (U.S.) Food and Drug Administration (FDA) for use in the U.S., which means that a doctor cannot prescribe this drug. The purpose of this study is to evaluate the long-term safety of darusentan in subjects with resistant systolic hypertension despite treatment with full doses of three or more antihypertensive medications, including a diuretic."
    },
